## Why This Matters

### For Mechanistic Interpretability

Demonstrates that confound-controlled evaluation is essential. Perfect metrics on tiny datasets are not validation; they are red flags for overfitting.

### For AI Safety

Shows that activation-space monitoring methods can be extended to novel domains, but requires careful validation before any operational claims.

### For Biosecurity

Suggests that semantic task distinctions may encode in model representations, but does not demonstrate robust threat detection capability.

